44,44,38,29,24,0,44,47,37]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bf4 O-O
6. e3 c5 7. dxc5 ({Hamless is} 7. cxd5 {when Black's simplest reaction is} Nxd5
8. Nxd5 {White's main move.} ({After} 8. Bg3 Nc6 9. Bd3 cxd4 10. exd4 Bf6 {
, we reach a typical IQP position when White's dark-squared bishop is a bit
