} 9. a3 Nc6 10. dxc5 Qxc5 11. Rc1 Qa5+) 9... Qxc5 10. a3 {White should waste
time for this move.} ({The alternative} 10. Bd3 {runs into} Qa5+ 11. Ke2 Nc6 {
[%cal Gf8d8] followed by ...Rd8. Quite obviously, the white king is badly
placed in the centre.}) 10... Nc6 11. Rc1 Qa5+ 12. Qd2 Qxd2+ 13. Nxd2 Bd7 $11 {
with equality.}) (7. Be2 dxc4 8. Bxc4 cxd4 9. Nxd4 {This is the most ambitious
