the d5-square under control.}) 9... Nbd7 {[%cal Ge6e5]} 10. Bg3 Bb4 {[%csl Rg3]
[%cal Gb4c3,Gb2c3,Gf6e4,Ge4g3] As we are going to witness again, the threat of
spoiling White's pawn structure with ...Bb4 followed by ...Bxc3 is the best
way to play in this structure. In such a case, Black's better structure will
compensate for the activity of White's pieces. A possible line would be} 11. Qc2
Bxc3+ 12. Qxc3 Ne4 13. Qa3 Nxg3 14. hxg3 Nf6 15. O-O Bd7 $11 {with equality.})
(7. Bd3 dxc4 {is a transposition to 7.Be2.}) 7... Bxc5 8. Rc1 {This is a
