) 16... Bxb5 17. cxd5 (17. cxb5 Nd7 18. Be2 Rc2 $132) 17... Bxd3 18. Rxd3 exd5
$11 {With equality.}) (8. Be2 dxc4 {transposes to the line 8.Bd3 dxc4.}) 8...
Nc6 9. a3 dxc4 {This is one of the two possible moves here. The alternative is
9...Be7. While both options are equally good, 9...dxc4 is an immediate
