Rxe4 27. Kc2 Nc4 $132) 19... Rec8 $5 {This is my novelty. It's more reliable
compared to 19...f5.} (19... f5 20. Nxc5 Nxc5 21. f3 Rac8 22. O-O {This time
White manages to secure his king. Black is still very active and close to
equal, but I think that this line is dangerous for us.} e4 23. Rd5 (23. Bf4 $14
{is a possible improvement}) 23... Ne6 24. Rxf5 (24. h4 $14) 24... exf3 25.
R1xf3 Nxg5 26. Rxg5 Rxc4 {1/2 (77) Karjakin,S (2748)-Nakamura,H (2754) Zagreb
2019}) 20. Rc2 (20. g4 Bf8 21. Rc2 {leads to the main line}) (20. Nxc5 Rxc5 21.
Be7 Rxc4 22. Ke2 f6 $11 {Black is out of danger}) 20... Bf8 21. g4 h5 $5 {
A useful move. Black is freeing the h7-square for the king. At the same time,
exchanging pawns will simplify the defence.} 22. h3 hxg4 23. hxg4 b5 24. Bh4 f6
25. Ke2 ({Another idea to put pressure on the kingside can be} 25. Bg3 Rab8 26.
